    "content_hash": "63e40313ff8f0ad4",
    "department": "General \u0026 Administrative",
    "description": "I'm Kristen Nolan https://www.linkedin.com/in/kristenenolan/, VP Accounting at Teamworks. I came up through the Controller seat myself, so I know exactly what this role demands — and more importantly, what makes it different from most Controller positions you'll come across.\n\nTeamworks is a late-stage, high-growth sports technology company serving professional leagues, collegiate athletic departments, Olympic programs, and military organizations worldwide. We're scaling fast, navigating M\u0026A activity, and building toward significant financial milestones. The accounting function needs to keep pace — and that means bringing in a Controller who can own it.\n\n\nTHE ROLE\n\n - Own the monthly close process end-to-end — identify opportunities to make it faster and more accurate, then execute on them\n\n - Lead all accounting workstreams through M\u0026A activity, including purchase accounting (ASC 805), opening balance sheets, and financial integration — this is active, recurring work across multiple deals, not a one-time event\n\n - Manage multi-entity consolidations, multi-currency accounting, and international statutory compliance across a footprint that continues to grow through acquisition\n\n - Build and strengthen internal controls, systems, and processes that scale with the company's growth — and position us well for future audit and financing events\n\n - Drive cross-functional partnership with FP\u0026A, RevOps, Legal, and functional leadership — translating complex accounting topics into clear financial insights that inform real decisions\n\n - Develop and grow the accounting team, building toward the scale and structure the business needs\n\n\nWHAT I'M LOOKING FOR\n\n\nWHAT YOU MUST BRING\n\n - Active CPA license — this is non-negotiable\n\n - 8–10 years of progressive accounting experience, including meaningful time in public accounting — Big 4 or large regional firm strongly preferred; the technical foundation this role requires comes from that environment\n\n - Prior experience as a Controller or Assistant Controller at a SaaS or tech company — you need to have sat in this seat before\n\n - Hands-on M\u0026A experience, specifically purchase accounting (ASC 805) — you've led these workstreams, not supported them from the sidelines\n\n - Strong technical accounting knowledge across ASC 606, ASC 718, ASC 350, multi-entity consolidations, and international accounting\n\n - Experience building or materially improving internal controls in a scaling company\n\n - Experience leading an external audit process — you've owned the relationship with auditors and managed the process end-to-end\n\n - People management experience — you've led or mentored an accounting team\n\n - ERP proficiency, with Intacct experience strongly preferred\n\n - Based in the Eastern Timezone — this role is fully remote\n\n\nEVEN BETTER IF\n\n - You've been through a financing event — Series D+, a debt raise, or IPO readiness — and know what it takes to get a company prepared\n\n - You’ve worked directly with lenders or investors on reporting requirements and covenant compliance\n\n - You have experience integrating financial systems and collaborating closely with FP\u0026A on planning and reporting\n\n - You’ve managed international statutory compliance across multiple jurisdictions\n\n\nWHY THIS ROLE\n\nMost Controller roles ask you to maintain the books. This one asks you to build something. With ongoing M\u0026A activity, an external audit to lead, international expansion in the picture, and a cross-functional leadership team that genuinely wants a seat at the table for Finance — the scope here is real and it grows with you. This is a rare chance to shape how a finance function is built from the inside.\n\n\n\nABOUT TEAMWORKS\n\nWe're the Operating System for Sports™, powering 6,500+ organizations worldwide, from collegiate programs to every major pro league. Founded in 2006, we've evolved from a messaging tool for college football into the leading sports tech platform, with 500+ global teammates building the future of sports tech. Our solutions span Personnel, Coaching, Performance, Operations, and Intelligence - helping teams recruit smarter, train better, stay compliant, and win.\n\nTeamworks is an equal opportunity employer - if you live our core values every day and are honest, hardworking, humble, committed, innovative, and an all-around exceptional person, you'll thrive at Teamworks. We are committed to building a diverse and inclusive workforce and take affirmative action to not discriminate based on race, religion, color, national origin, ancestry, physical disability, mental disability, medical condition, genetic information, marital status, sex, gender, gender identity, gender expression, age, sexual orientation, veteran or military status, or any other legally protected characteristics. This policy applies to all employment practices within our organization, including but not limited to recruiting, hiring, promotion, termination, compensation, benefits, and training. Teamworks is committed to providing reasonable accommodations for candidates with disabilities who need assistance during the hiring process. To request a reasonable accommodation, please email talent@teamworks.com.\n\n\nTo all recruitment agencies: Teamworks does not accept agency resumes. Please do not forward resumes to our jobs alias, Teamworks employees or any other organization location. Teamworks is not responsible for any fees related to unsolicited resumes.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
